        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-06-26T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-06-26T23:00:00-05:00" n="479" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d479">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.50 Recovery/6–2748: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-06-27T13:00:00+09:00">June 27, 1948—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 27—8:43 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1165. In conference this morning with Foreign Office, Embassy’s revised text
                    article IV (old numbering) rejected. RefEmbtel 1163 and 1164, June 27, 11 a.m.
                    Embassy requests authority <hi rend="italic">in extremis</hi> to revert to
                    original language this article and secure strict and detailed interpretative
                    commitment in agreed minute of negotiators.</p>
                <p>Sent Dept 1165; repeated Shanghai 536.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
